r = 4 + 2\cos(2\theta)
f(\theta)
\delta\theta
\frac 12 f(\theta)^2 \sin\delta\theta\simeq  \frac 12 f(\theta)^2 \delta\theta 
 A = \frac 12\int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2} f(\theta)^2 d\theta. 
 A = \int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2} d\theta \int_{0}^{f(\theta)} rdr = \int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2} d\theta \frac {f(\theta)^2}{2} = \frac 12 \int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2} f(\theta)^2 d\theta. 
A = \frac 12 \int_0^{2\pi} (4+2\cos2\theta)^2 d\theta =  2\pi \frac{16 + 0 + 2}2 = 18\pi. 
